reply: In Pseudo Code, we don't start the counting with 0 first of all. So the first element is counted as 1 and the second element is count as 2 and so on. So, when we start our algorithm, we start with 2 because the first element would be already there, if not then we'll have nothing to compare with in the start. In the pseudo code, you can see we set i<- j-1 so if we start with 1 then i will be 0 which is out of bounds for the array. We initially take 1st element as our reference element around which we will insert our elements.
